<p>Iâ€™ve split dactlâ€™s <code>_config.yml</code> into two parts. First part should be configured by you, second contains important Jekyll &amp; build settings and you should leave it alone, unless you know what you are doing.
&lt;!â€“-break-â€“&gt;</p>

<p>Letâ€™s go through each line in the first, configurable part:</p>

<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Base blog settings
blog:
  title                      : dactl
  description                : &gt;
                               this should contain a proper description
# Layout configuration
  logo_path                  : "assets/img/dactl.svg" # path to logo file
  search_path                : # "yourgitusername.github.io"
                               # needed for searchbox in archive page
